n of the national bank of denmark this classic design is still in production today by danish company vola style and legacyedit according to r craig miller author of design  what modern was jacobsen’s work is an important and original contribution both to modernism and to the specific place denmark and the scandinavian countries have in the modern movement and continues one might in fact argue that much of what the modern movement stands for would have been lost and simply forgotten if scandinavian designers and architects like arne jacobsen would not have added that humane element to it arne jacobsen is noted for his sense of proportion indeed he himself saw this as one of the main features of his work in an interview he said the proportion is exactly what makes the beautiful ancient egyptian temples  and if we look at some of the most admired buildings of the renaissance and baroque we notice that they were all wellproportioned here is the basic thing selected worksedit alléhusene housing gentofte  st catherines college oxfordundergraduate rooms and belltowerview from west danish embassy london architectureedit bellevue beach klampenborg denmark  bellavista residential complex klampenborg copenhagen – bellevue theatre and restaurant klampenborg – skovshoved petrol station skovshoved copenhagen  stelling house  gammeltorv copenhagen – søllerød town hall with flemming lassen søllerød copenhagen – århus city hall with erik møller århus – søholm i – ii and iii terraced houses klampenborg rødovre town hall rødovre denmark – alléhusene housing gentofte copenhagen – glostrup town hall glostrup copenhagen  munkegaard school copenhagen  sas royal hotel copenhagen – toms chocolate factory ballerup copenhagen  national bank of denmark copenhagen – landskrona sportshall landskrona sweden  st catherines college oxford uk – mainz city hall mainz germany – christianeum school hamburg germany – hew vattenfall europe hamburg germany  royal danish embassy london uk – parliament hous